# CSRD Architecture Rules

## 1. Planning and execution MUST stay separated

The scenario layer (`+csrd/+blocks/+scenario`) produces `TxPlan`, `RxPlan`, `GlobalLayout`.
The factory layer (`+csrd/+factories`) instantiates classes and runs them. Factories must
NOT inject random parameters into a half-empty plan during execution - every Tx in the plan
already knows its modulation, message type, bandwidth window, and timing pattern.

If a factory finds itself reaching for `randi` to "fill in" a missing field, that field is
a planner bug; fix the planner instead of papering over it in the factory.

## 2. Receiver-centric frequency allocation

All carrier frequencies live inside the receiver's observable range `[-Fs/2, +Fs/2]` (relative
to the receiver center). The planner allocates carriers in this window; the channel + receiver
chain enforces it. Do not store absolute RF carriers in segment signals - keep them as
`FrequencyOffset` relative to the receiver.

## 3. Data contracts (segment signal struct)

A modulator/transmit-impair output struct MUST include:
- `.Signal` (samples x antennas, complex)
- `.SampleRate` (Hz, > 0)
- `.FrequencyOffset` (Hz, relative to Rx center)
- `.Bandwidth` (Hz, occupied)
- `.SegmentId` (string, unique within frame; legacy `.SegmentID` accepted for read-only)

A channel output adds `.PathLoss`, `.LinkDistance`, optional `.AppliedPathLoss`,
`.ChannelModel`, `.ChannelInfo`.

A receiver-side annotation source MUST split into `.Planned`, `.Realized`, `.Temporal`,
`.Spatial`, `.LinkBudget`, `.Channel` substructures. See `csrd-physics.mdc` rule 2.

## 4. Scenario-skip exceptions are first class

Use `csrd.utils.scenario.isScenarioSkipException(ME)` everywhere a `try/catch` may need to
distinguish "skip this scenario, keep going" from "abort the run". Recognised tokens
(substring match on identifier): `SkipScenario`, `NoBuildingData`, `NoValidPaths`.

```matlab
% GOOD
catch ME_step
    if csrd.utils.scenario.isScenarioSkipException(ME_step)
        rethrow(ME_step);
    end
    % swallow generic / transient errors here
end
```

## 5. Cache keys MUST encode all sources of state

Cached `matlab.System` instances are stateful. Always include enough identity in the cache
key to prevent state leakage between independent links. RayTracing channel blocks in
particular MUST be cached per `Tx-Rx` pair; sharing them across links corrupts every link
except the most recently configured one.
